In this lesson, Part 2, we will discuss the more complex auctions that result when responder does not have support.

In all of these lessons, I will assume the reader uses basic hand evaluation techniques. That is, he or she uses the standard 4-3-2-1 method for counting HCP and makes small adjustments for either shortness or length. I now teach, and prefer, the more accurate Bergen methodology, but, because it is not familiar to everyone, I will not use it in these lessons. Now, let me begin the lesson on when the responder does not have support for openers's suit.
 
|
