AT|If opener has a balanced hand (5-3-3-2, or 5-4-2-2 with scattered honors) and a minimum or medium hand, he should pass. With a 6-card major, opener should rebid it. With an unbalanced hand, partner should bid the second suit, asking you to pass with 3-card support. The one exception is that with 5 hearts and 4 spades and a minimum, opener should pass, because the auction 1H-1NT-2S is a reverse, showing a medium or maximum hand. Let us look at a few examples.

