fp||cp|8|AT|^B@2^Y@3^*BHoward: ^*N|cp||at|These are the most complicated auctions, because you, as captain, need to determine both the best strain (which suit or NT), and whether or not your side has game (if opener has a medium hand, 15-17, or maximum hand, 18+). The basic approach is for you to bid a new suit (forcing another bid from opener), and then invite or bid game based on opener's next bid. Let's look at some specific cases:|
