HT|t|at|^B{|ia|,1hp2cp2d|at|}|ht|S|AT|^m@2^Y@3On the other hand if opener bids a non-reverse new suit,|HT|T|AT|^m@2^Y@3you can correct back to the original major with 2-card support, or raise to 3 with good support for opener's second suit. You should be reluctant to pass because opener could have a medium hand.  |
