HT|h|AT|^m@2^Y@3and see why it promises 5 hearts.|ht|l|at|^B@2^Y@3If you, as responder, only have 4 hearts, you virtually always have a 4-card minor. You don't have 4 spades (you would have raised), so, unless you are exactly 3-4-3-3, you have to have a 4-card minor. Therefore, you bid your 4-card minor. Opener now has the opportunity to bid 2H over your minor. Therefore, requiring responder to have a 5-card heart suit in order to bid 2H makes it easier for your side to determine how many hearts there are between the two hands.|
